==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marksman
<hw>Marks"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Marksmen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Earlier
<ets>markman</ets>; <ets>mark</ets> + <ets>man</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One skillful to hit a mark with a missile; one who shoots well.
especially with a pistol or rifle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who makes his mark, instead of
writing his name, in signing documents.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marksmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
